Package gov.sandia.geotess.extensions.earthinterface

Class GeoTessMetaDataEarthInterface

java.lang.Object
gov.sandia.geotess.GeoTessMetaData
gov.sandia.geotess.extensions.earthinterface.GeoTessMetaDataEarthInterface
public class GeoTessMetaDataEarthInterface
extends GeoTessMetaData
An extension of the base class GeoTessMetaData object that contains an additional container that holds the EarthInterface layer interfaces used by any model referencing this meta data object. This derived type forces all layer interface names to be precisely named and ordered according to the EarthInteface enum specification.
Author:
jrhipp

    • setEarthInterfaceLayers

      public void setEarthInterfaceLayers​(java.lang.String interfaceLayerNames) throws java.io.IOException
      Specify the names of the interfaces, and optionally, the layers supported by the model. Interface names must match entries in the EarthInterface enum. Layer names can be defined preceding each interface name if desired. If layer names are not input they are automatically assigned to the string interface name + "_LAYER". If the interface names are not ordered from the deepest interface to the shallowest and IOException is thrown.
      Parameters:
      interfaceLayerNames - The names of each interface supported by this model, and optionally, each layer name. If provided, the layer names must precede the interface names. Only interface names that match the interfaces names defined in the EarthInterface enum are allowed.
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException

    • getInterfaceIndex

      public int getInterfaceIndex​(java.lang.String... majorInterfaces)
      Retrieve the index of the interface with the specified name. If majorInterfaces can be parsed to an integer, then that value is returned. If not, then the index of the interface with the specified name is returned.

      If more than one name is supplied, the first one that can be successfully interpreted as either an integer index or a valid interface name is returned.

      The ability to supply alternative names is useful. For example, some models call the top of the crust "CRUST" while in other models the top of the crust is called "UPPER_CRUST". If both are requested using this method, the correct index will be returned.

      Overrides:
      getInterfaceIndex in class GeoTessMetaData
      Parameters:
      majorInterfaces - String
      Returns:
      int

    • setModelLayers

      public void setModelLayers​(java.lang.String... layers) throws java.io.IOException
      A generic layer name set function for any type of extended GeoTessMetaData object. This method is over-ridden by the derived class to fill in specific types of layer name information. In this case the layer names must be prescribed so as to adhere to the ordered structure of the EarthInterface enum list.
